          <h2>おっす!</h2>
          <p>
            Born and raised in Seattle and now based in Tokyo, I’m a full-stack web developer with a background in international affairs, HR, and teaching. Those experiences shape how I approach software: putting people first, communicating clearly across cultures, and caring about how things actually feel to use. I enjoy building practical, inclusive web apps with clean design, thoughtful UX, and an emphasis on reliability and maintainability.
          </p>
          <p>
            Outside of coding, I’m usually chasing after a high-energy four-year-old, cycling Tokyo’s backstreets, following motorsports and car culture, hunting down good craft beer, or getting out of the city to camp and hike around Japan. Those rhythms help me stay grounded and observant, and they often feed back into how I think about usability and design.
